mes:
"Hello world!"

In JavaScript that looks like:

```js
function HelloWorld() {
    console.log("Hello World!");
}
HelloWorld();
``` The air hung heavy with the scent of ozone and cheap ramen.  Rain lashed against the grimy windows of the internet cafe, blurring the neon signs of the city into a shimmering kaleidoscope.  Jin sat hunched over a battered laptop, fingers flying across the keyboard.  The rhythmic *click-clack* of keys was punctuated by the occasional frustrated sigh.  Across the small, cluttered table, a figure stirred. The air hung thick and heavy with the scent of ozone and burnt coffee.  Rain lashed against the grimy windows of the "Codex Cafe," blurring the neon signs of the city into shimmering streaks.  Inside, the only illumination came from the flickering screens of a dozen laptops, each casting a pale, ethereal glow on the faces hunched over them.  You, Jin, sat at a small table near the back, your own laptop displaying the now-familiar "Hello World!" message.  A half-eaten croissant lay abandoned on your plate, crumbs scattering like fallen stars across the worn Formica tabletop.  A figure approached, their footsteps muffled by the carpet.  They paused beside your table, their shadow falling across your screen.

